    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are leaning heavily on power and high-leverage spots today, with **Yordan Alvarez** (74.41) and **Trea Turner** (70.46) anchoring the lineup. **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a favorable matchup against Cecconi (4.19 xERA) and an elite xwOBA profile, while **Trea Turner** remains our premier offensive threat despite the moderate efficiency hit from a high-control pitcher in Rea. **Kyle Schwarber** also warrants a strong start (69.69) as his elite xwOBA pairs perfectly with the favorable matchup against Rea, mitigating the inherent risks of a standard platoon dynamic. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (60.49) is a compelling play today; while he faces the historically stingy Nola, his massive platoon advantage (+14%) and inherent speed profile make him an essential engine for our stolen base targets, even with the warning regarding Nola\u2019s elite ability to hold runners.\n\nWe are navigating a tight threshold for our bench, where **Dillon Dingler** (36.10) served as the primary rotation consideration. Despite benefiting from a friendly park factor, **Dillon Dingler** fell short of our 40.0 floor due to a poor platoon setup against Gray, ultimately pushing us to prioritize **Caleb Durbin** (50.05) and **Colt Keith** (50.63) for their steadier roles in the top-to-middle order. We are maintaining caution with **Victor Scott II** (43.78) and **Luke Raley** (44.76); their scores are bolstered by favorable defensive windows\u2014specifically the slow delivery speeds of Meyer and Ginn which invite aggressive baserunning\u2014but they remain marginal plays that require monitoring. We continue to track **Christian Yelich** on the IL, hoping for a return to the active roster to bolster our outfield production, as the current bench remains thin on immediate impact depth.",
